Space Shuttle Sequences by Eric Zwirnmann.
August 4th, 1989

This Arced file should contian the following:
			SHUTTL1S.SEQ
			SHUTTL2S.SEQ
			READ_ME .DOC

The animation files (SEQ) each require at least 1 MEG  and ANIMATE4.SEQ.
Feel free to pass these files around... all that I ask is that this readme file
is included with the shuttle animations.

I would like to thank Jeffrey Gooden (CAVID tm) for his continuous "nagging"
and asking me when I was going to finish with the shuttle and give him a
copy.  Little does he know that there is a lot more to come!

Just a little bit about these animations.
The Space Shuttle took me aproximately 2 weeks to design and perfect.  The
animations took 24 (yes twenty-four) hours to create.  That's 48 hours without
a computer (geeze!).  The original (full screen) animations each required
2 Megs to be seen.  They were however created on my Mega 4 ST.

Look for more great animations in the not so distant future.

Mail all comments to:      E.ZWIRNMANN  (GEnie)


